[src:mesa-graphics-stack/gallium3d] ARM Panfrost is mostly improved with many modules.
[src:mesa-graphics-stack/gallium3d] Shared virtual memory is possible for OpenCL in Nouveau with Pascal and higher.
[src:mesa-graphics-stack/gallium3d] 4th Version of 2020 is 20.3. v3d and v3dv are new drivers for OpenGL and Vulkan 1.0 with Broadcom hardware like Raspberry Pi 4.
[src:mesa-graphics-stack/gallium3d] OpenCL 1.2 is full supported in clover module.
[src:mesa-graphics-stack/gallium3d] LLVMpipe virtual driver support now OpenGL 4.5+ with 4.6 in view.
[src:mesa-graphics-stack/gallium3d] Lavapipe (originally called Vallium) as Vulkan Tree of LLVMpipe is merged.
[src:mesa-graphics-stack/gallium3d] In Mesa 21.0 d3d12 will be merged with OpenGL 3.0 to 3.3.
[src:mesa-graphics-stack/gallium3d] Microsoft and Collabora develops new emulation d3d12 in WSL2 to Windows 10 with Direct 3D 12.
[src:mesa-graphics-stack/gallium3d] An acceleration of factor 2 to 5 is done in Benchmark SPECviewperf with improved OpenGL Code.
[src:mesa-graphics-stack/gallium3d] Many Mesa 21.0 features improves performance.
[src:mesa-graphics-stack/gallium3d] New Release 21.0.0 is public since 11 March 2021.
[src:mesa-graphics-stack/gallium3d] Mesa 21.1 is second release of year 2021.
[src:mesa-graphics-stack/gallium3d] OpenGL 4.6+ and OpenGL ES 3.1+ is available for Zink.
[src:mesa-graphics-stack/gallium3d] AMD Driver 600g can change to NIR with more possibilities for old Radeon HD 5000 and 6000 cards.
[src:mesa-graphics-stack/gallium3d] Qualcomm Turnip reaches Vulkan 1.1+ and software emulation Lavapipe Vulkan 1.1+.
[src:mesa-graphics-stack/gallium3d] Google VirtIO GPU Driver Venus with Vulkan 1.2+ is merged in experimental state with low performance in mesa main tree.
[src:mesa-graphics-stack/gallium3d] Mesa 21.2 is third release of year 2021.
