[src:mesa-graphics-stack/gallium3d] Initial support started for ARM Apple M1 with new driver Asahi.
[src:mesa-graphics-stack/gallium3d] Proposed architectural changes involve migrating legacy drivers to a standalone "classic" tree to streamline maintenance and bug fixing for the modern **Gallium3D** framework.
[src:mesa-graphics-stack/gallium3d] A significant complication remains the **Intel i965** driver, which provides critical support for popular legacy hardware—including the **Intel Haswell** microarchitecture—and maintains compatibility with **Windows 10**.
[src:mesa-graphics-stack/gallium3d] A new Gallium3D driver Crocus for Intel Gen 4 Graphics to Haswell is here in development to complete here the gallium3D area with possible split in the next time of year 2021.
[src:mesa-graphics-stack/gallium3d] Amber branch is for old drivers without Gallium 3D Functions like Radeon R200, intel i915 and 965 with actual version 21.3.9.
[src:mesa-graphics-stack/gallium3d] In Version 22.0 Classic drivers are retired.
[src:mesa-graphics-stack/gallium3d] Vulkan 1.3 is available for Intel Anvil and AMD RADV.
[src:mesa-graphics-stack/gallium3d] Microsoft introduces new driver „Dozen“ for WSL 2 in early development stage as Vulkan over d3d12 in Mesa 22.1.
[src:mesa-graphics-stack/gallium3d] RustiCL is available at 22.3 with official OpenCL 3.0 Conformance for Intel XE Graphics.
[src:mesa-graphics-stack/gallium3d] Performance is equal and better to AMD ROCm with AMD 6700 XT Card.
[src:mesa-graphics-stack/gallium3d] A main development target of Mesa 23.0 was ray tracing for Vulkan.
[src:mesa-graphics-stack/gallium3d] Microsoft develops the Dozen driver for Vulkan in WSL.
